ies and ensure job acceptance within the timeline</li></ol></li><li>Learning & Development <ol><li>Plan manage all learning and development activities (onboarding new hire, trainings, workshop, webminar, etc)</li><li>Deliver post training evaluation to review training effectiveness</li></ol></li><li>Employee Engagement: <ol><li>Initiate engagement activities to build a positive working environment</li></ol></li></ul><div><div> </div><div><strong>HR Operations</strong></div><ul><li>HR information system <ol><li>Manage internal HR information system: account creation, employee database and movement update, HRIS training for new hires</li><li>Be prudent and discreet on employee’s data confidentiality</li></ol></li><li>Reward & Remuneration <ol><li>Assist HR manager in developing competitive remuneration scheme</li><li>Ensure all reports and payments for remuneration are done in timely manner</li></ol></li><li>Industrial Relations <ol><li>Ensure the compliance of all HR policies</li><li>Manage dispute resolution</li></ol></li><li>Responsible for all internal HR communication</li></ul><div> </div><div><strong>4. JOB REQUIREMENTS</strong></div></div></div><ul><li>Candidate must possess at least Bachelor\'s Degree in Business Studies/Administration/Management, Human Resource Management, Psychology or equivalent.</li><li>Required language(s): English, Bahasa Indonesia</li><li>At least 5 Year(s) of working experience in the related field is required for this position, preferably in HR retail industry</li><li>Required Skill(s): high intergrity, ogranizational skills, work ethics, analytical skills, communication skils, coaching, training, decision making skills, conflict management, business management, adaptive, eager to learn, advanced proficiency in computer skill</li><li>Preferably Manager/Assistant Manager specialized in Human Resources or equivalent.</li></ul></div></div></div>', 1, '2020-10-13', '2020-09-13 20:44:40'),
